main event: An unidentified flying object was observed both on ground radar and visually in Warpke, West Germany on January 2, 1962.
interesting points: The observation lasted from 2215 to 2300 hours,The object was noted to be maneuvering and turning towards West Germany,The report suggested the object might be an astronomical light or possibly an aircraft,The visual sighting was confirmed by staff at a nearby location,The evaluation of source reliability was marked as unknown but good.
witness description: staff of UHF location camera station
